ABIERTO.def: Allowing access, passage, or a view through an empty space; not closed or blocked up.

ACTIVO.def: Engaging or ready to engage in physically energetic pursuits.

ADMITIR.def: Confess to be true or to be the case.

AGUA.def: A colorless, transparent, odorless, tasteless liquid that forms the seas, lakes, rivers, and rain and is the basis of the fluids of living organisms.

AIRE.def: The invisible gaseous substance surrounding the earth.

AMOR.def: An intense feeling of deep affection.

ANADIR.def: Join something to something else so as to increase the size.

ANCHO.def: Of great or more than average width.

ANO.def: The time taken by a planetary body to make one revolution around its sun.

APLICAR.def: Make a formal application or request.

APUESTA.def: An act of risking a sum of money on the outcome of a future event.

ARBOL.def: A woody perennial plant, typically having a single stem or trunk growing to a considerable height and bearing lateral branches at some distance from the ground.

AREA.def: A region or part of a town, a country, or the world.

ARTE.def: The expression or application of human creative skill and imagination.

AYUDA.def: Make it easier for (someone) to do something by offering one's services or resources.

AZUL.def: Of a color intermediate between green and violet.

BANCO.def: A financial establishment that invests money deposited by customers.

BARCO.def: A small vessel for traveling over water.

BIEN.def: In a good or satisfactory way.

BLANCO.def: Of the color of milk or fresh snow, due to the reflection of all visible rays of light; the opposite of black.

BOLA.def: A solid or hollow spherical or egg-shaped object.

BOLSA.def: A container made of flexible material.

BRAZO.def: Each of the two upper limbs of the human body from the shoulder to the hand.

BRUJA.def: Mujer a la que se le atribuyen poderes mágicos y sobrenaturales, en la mayoría de los casos empleados para hacer el mal.

BUENO.def: To be desired or approved of.

CAER.def: Move downward and typically rapidly and freely without control, from a higher to a lower level.

CAJA.def: A container with a flat base and sides, typically square or rectangular and having a lid.

CALOR.def: The quality of being hot; high temperature.

CAMA.def: A piece of furniture for sleep or rest.

CAMINO.def: A method, style, or manner of doing something.

CAMPO.def: An area of open land, especially one planted with crops or used for pasture.

CAPAZ.def: Having the power, skill, or means to do something.

CARA.def: The front part of a person's head from the forehead to the chin, or the corresponding part in an animal.

CARGA.def: Demand (an amount) as a price from someone for a service rendered or goods supplied.

CASA.def: A building for human habitation, especially one that is lived in by a family or small group of people.

CAUSA.def: A person or thing that gives rise to an action, phenomenon, or condition.

CENTRO.def: The middle point of a circle or sphere, equidistant from every point on the circumference or surface.

CERCA.def: At or to a short distance away; close by.

CERRAR.def: Move or be moved so as to cover an opening.

CINCO.def: Equivalent to the product of one and five; one more than four.

CLARO.def: Easy to perceive, understand, or interpret.

CLASE.def: A set or category of things having some property or attribute in common and differentiated from others by kind, type, or quality.

COGER.def: Intercept and hold (something which has been thrown, propelled, or dropped).

COMER.def: Put (food) into the mouth and chew and swallow it.

COMIDA.def: Any nutritious substance that people or animals eat or drink or that plants absorb in order to maintain life and growth.

CONTAR.def: Communicate information, facts, or news to someone in spoken or written words.

COPIA.def: A thing made to be similar or identical to another.

CORRER.def: Move at a speed faster than a walk, never having both or all the feet on the ground at the same time.

CRUZ.def: A mark, object, or figure formed by two short intersecting lines or pieces (+ or x).

CUATRO.def: Equivalent to the product of two and two; one more than three.

CUBRIR.def: Put something over or on top of (something else), typically in order to protect or conceal it.

CUIDAR.def: The provision of what is necessary for the health, welfare, maintenance, and protection of someone or something.

CURSO.def: An area of land or water on which a race is held.

DAR.def: Freely transfer the possession of (something) to (someone); hand over to.

DECIR.def: Utter words so as to convey information, an opinion, a feeling or intention, or an instruction.

DESEO.def: Feel or express a strong desire or hope for something that is not easily attainable; want something that cannot or probably will not happen.

DIEZ.def: Equivalent to the product of five and two; one more than nine.

DINERO.def: A current medium of exchange in the form of coins and banknotes; coins and banknotes collectively.

DOBLE.def: Consisting of two equal, identical, or similar parts or things.

DORMIR.def: A condition of body and mind which typically recurs for several hours every night, in which the nervous system is relatively inactive, the eyes closed, the postural muscles relaxed, and consciousness practically suspended.

DOS.def: Equivalent to the sum of one and one; one more than one; 2.

DUDA.def: A feeling of uncertainty or lack of conviction.

DURO.def: Solid, firm, and resistant to pressure; not easily broken or bent.

EDAD.def: The length of time that a person has lived.

EQUIPO.def: A group of players forming one side in a competitive game or sport.

ESO.def: Used to identify a specific person or thing observed by the speaker.

ESPOSA.def: A married woman considered in relation to her husband.

ESTE.def: Used to identify a specific person or thing close at hand, being indicated or experienced, or for the first time.

GAS.def: An air-like fluid substance which expands freely to fill any space available, irrespective of its quantity.

HOY.def: On or during the present day.

LEY.def: The system of rules which a particular country or community recognizes as regulating the actions of its members and which it may enforce by the imposition of penalties.

LUZ.def: The natural agent that stimulates sight and makes things visible.

PERRO.def: Variedad doméstica del lobo de muchas y diversas razas

POR.def: For each (used with units to express a rate).
